user_prompt_template:
CHAPTER TO EXPAND:
{current_chapter_json}

PROJECT CONTEXT:
Life Event: {life_event}
Document: {document_title}
Audience: {audience}
Tone: {tone}
Context: {context}

Expand this chapter into complete, purpose-built operational content for {domain_name}.

FOR EACH WORKSHEET IN THE CHAPTER PLAN:
First, decide its format:
  → Is it collecting a LIST of similar items?                       = "table"
  → Is it CHECKING OFF discrete action items?                       = "checklist"
  → Is it COMPARING two parties/states side by side?                = "two-column"
  → Is it PLANNING, ASSESSING, or ANALYZING in narrative form?      = "form"

NARRATIVE REQUIREMENTS (MINIMUM 2000 words, target 2500+):
  • Do NOT open with generic explanation of why this domain matters. Begin with operational specifics immediately.
  • Include specific Florida Gulf Coast regulatory references, statutes, county agencies, or named professional bodies where applicable to {life_event}
  • Include 2-3 concrete failure scenarios with specific dollar amounts, timeframes, or legal consequences — not vague warnings
  • Include decision trees or explicit if/then logic for the 2-3 most common judgment calls an operator faces in this domain
  • Step-by-step operational approach with named phases and explicit dependencies between steps
  • Escalation guidance: name the specific professional type, the precise trigger condition, and the consequence of not escalating
  • Key decisions the operator must make, with the criteria for each option laid out explicitly

WORKSHEET DATA STRUCTURE BY FORMAT:

REPEAT-USE AND CROSS-REFERENCE FIELDS — required on every worksheet:
  repeat_use (boolean): Set to true if this worksheet is designed to be used on an ongoing or recurring basis (e.g. monthly tracking tables, recurring review checklists, periodic audit forms). Set to false for one-time setup worksheets.
  cross_references (array of strings): List the exact titles of OTHER worksheets in this chapter (or other chapters) whose output directly feeds into this worksheet, or whose completion is a prerequisite for this one. Leave as an empty array if no dependencies exist. Do not reference the current worksheet itself.

  layout: "table"
    Required: table_columns (array of 3–7 specific column header strings)
    Required: table_row_count (integer, 10–14)
    Omit: sections, fields

  layout: "checklist"
    Required: checklist_items (array of 20–30 strings, each starting with a verb)
    Omit: sections, fields

  layout: "two-column"
    Required: left_column_label (string), right_column_label (string)
    Required: sections (3–4 sections, 3–5 fields each)
    Field types same as form layout

  layout: "form"
    Required: sections (3–5 sections with distinct operational purposes)
    Each section: section_id, section_title, instructions, fields (6–10)
    Each field: field_id, label, type, placeholder, required, options (if select)
    Valid types: text, textarea, date, number, boolean, select, multi-select

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "chapter_number": {chapter_number},
  "domain_id": "domain ID from the chapter plan",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter title from the plan",
  "narrative": "Full operational narrative — minimum 2000 words",
  "quick_reference_rules": [
    "Rule text — Rationale: why this rule exists. Trigger: when/what activates it. Risk: consequence of ignoring it."
  ],
  "worksheets": [
    {{
      "id": "ws-{chapter_number:02d}-a",
      "title": "Exact title from chapter plan",
      "layout": "table | checklist | two-column | form",
      "purpose": "One sentence operational purpose",
      "estimated_completion_time": "e.g. '30 minutes'",

      // If layout == table:
      "table_columns": ["Column 1", "Column 2", "Column 3"],
      "table_row_count": 12,

      // If layout == checklist:
      "checklist_items": ["Verify ...", "Confirm ...", "Obtain ..."],

      // If layout == two-column:
      "left_column_label": "Label for left column",
      "right_column_label": "Label for right column",

      // If layout == form or two-column:
      "sections": [
        {{
          "section_id": "s-01",
          "section_title": "Section title",
          "instructions": "Brief operator instructions",
          "fields": [
            {{
              "field_id": "f-001",
              "label": "Specific field label",
              "type": "text | textarea | date | number | boolean | select | multi-select",
              "placeholder": "Realistic specific example value",
              "required": true,
              "options": []
            }}
          ]
        }}
      ],
      "decision_gates": [
        {{
          "gate_id": "g-01",
          "gate_title": "Gate name",
          "condition": "Specific verifiable condition",
          "pass_action": "What to do when condition is met",
          "fail_action": "What to do when condition is not met",
          "blocks_completion": true
        }}
      ],
      "repeat_use": false,
      "cross_references": []
    }}
  ],
  "cascade_triggers": [
    "When [condition in this chapter], immediately trigger [action in other chapter/domain]"
  ]
}}
